components:

    tmp1:

        analysis_time: {type: string}

        family_name: {type: string}

        verdict: {type: string}

    tmp10:
      properties:
        file_type: {type: string}
        md5: {type: string}
        sha1: {type: string}
        sha256: {type: string}
        size_in_bytes: {type: string}
        ssdeep: {type: string}
      type: object
    tmp11:
      properties:
        success: {type: string}
      type: object
    tmp12:
      properties:
        success: {type: string}
      type: object
    tmp2:
      properties:
        success: {type: string}
      type: object
    tmp3:
      properties:
        success: {type: string}
      type: object
    tmp4:
      properties:
        file: {type: string}
      type: object
    tmp5:
      properties:
        result_url: {type: string}
        vaccine_file: {type: string}
      type: object
    tmp6:
      properties:
        analysis_id: {type: string}
        analysis_time: {type: string}
        analysis_url: {type: string}
        family_name: {type: string}
        is_private: {type: string}
        sha256: {type: string}
        sub_verdict: {type: string}
        verdict: {type: string}
      type: object
    tmp7:
      properties:
        analysis_id: {type: string}
        analysis_time: {type: string}
        analysis_url: {type: string}
        family_name: {type: string}
        is_private: {type: string}
        sha256: {type: string}
        sub_verdict: {type: string}
        verdict: {type: string}
      type: object
    tmp8:
      properties:
        analysis_analysis_id: {type: string}
        analysis_analysis_time: {type: string}
        analysis_analysis_url: {type: string}
        analysis_sha256: {type: string}
        analysis_sub_analysis_id: {type: string}
        analysis_sub_verdict: {type: string}
        analysis_verdict: {type: string}
        reused_genes_gene_count: {type: string}

    tmp9:

info:
  contact: {email: frikky@shuffler.io, name: '@frikkylikeme', url: 'https://twitter.com/frikkylikeme'}
  description: Automated generation of Intezer Analyze
  title: Intezer Analyze
  version: 1.0.0
  x-logo: data:image/png;base64,
openapi: 3.0.2
paths:
  tmp0:
    post:
      description: Analyze a file with Intezer Analyze
      parameters:
      - description: File attachment to analyze.
        example: ''
        in: query
        name: File Attachment
        required: true
        schema: {type: string}
      responses:
        '200':
          content:
            application/json:
              schema: {$ref: '#/components/schemas/tmp0'}
          description: Successful request
      summary: Intezer Analyze Analyze File from Attachment
  tmp1:
    post:
      description: Analyze a file by hash
      parameters:
      - description: MD5, SHA256 hash for file
        example: ''
        in: query
        name: Hash
        required: true
        schema: {type: string}
      responses:
        '200':
          content:
            application/json:
              schema: {$ref: '#/components/schemas/tmp1'}
          description: Successful request
      summary: Intezer Analyze Analyze by Hash
  tmp10:
    post:
      description: The Get Sub-Analysis task will retrieve a sub-analysis metadata
        by ID
      parameters:
      - description: The ID of an analysis
        example: 768a3ba4-d80a-4ca6-b87c-22f071495705
        in: query
        name: Analysis ID
        required: true
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: The ID of a sub-analysis
        example: 568a3ba4-d80a-4ca6-b87c-22f0712345
        in: query
        name: Sub-Analysis ID
        required: true
        schema: {type: string}
      responses:
        '200':
          content:
            application/json:
              schema: {$ref: '#/components/schemas/tmp10'}
          description: Successful request
      summary: Intezer Analyze Get Sub-Analysis Metadata By ID
  tmp11:
    post:
      description: Index a file in Intezer Analyze.
      parameters:
      - description: SHA256 to index.
        example: ''
        in: query
        name: SHA256
        required: true
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: 'The type of classification of this file, as follows: malicious
          or trusted. Defaults to `trusted`'
        example: ''
        in: query
        name: Index As
        required: false
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: The name of the family to index to, only available when indexing
          as malicious
        example: ''
        in: query
        name: Family Name
        required: false
        schema: {type: string}
      responses:
        '200':
          content:
            application/json:
              schema: {$ref: '#/components/schemas/tmp11'}
          description: Successful request
      summary: Intezer Analyze Index File by SHA256
  tmp12:
    post:
      description: Label a file in Intezer by SHA256.
      parameters:
      - description: SHA256 to index.
        example: ''
        in: query
        name: SHA256
        required: true
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: Label to apply to file.
        example: ''
        in: query
        name: Label
        required: true
        schema: {type: string}
      responses:
        '200':
          content:
            application/json:
              schema: {$ref: '#/components/schemas/tmp12'}
          description: Successful request
      summary: Intezer Analyze Label File
  tmp2:
    post:
      description: Delete a file from Intezer Analyze.
      parameters:
      - description: SHA256 of file to delete.
        example: ''
        in: query
        name: SHA256
        required: true
        schema: {type: string}
      responses:
        '200':
          content:
            application/json:
              schema: {$ref: '#/components/schemas/tmp2'}
          description: Successful request
      summary: Intezer Analyze Delete File by SHA256
  tmp3:
    post:
      description: Delete a file Index by hash
      parameters:
      - description: A SHA256 File hash.
        example: ''
        in: query
        name: SHA256
        required: true
        schema: {type: string}
      responses:
        '200':
          content:
            application/json:
              schema: {$ref: '#/components/schemas/tmp3'}
          description: Successful request
      summary: Intezer Analyze Delete Index by SHA256
  tmp4:
    post:
      description: Download a file from Intezer Analyze.
      parameters:
      - description: SHA256 to index.
        example: ''
        in: query
        name: SHA256
        required: true
        schema: {type: string}
      responses:
        '200':
          content:
            application/json:
              schema: {$ref: '#/components/schemas/tmp4'}
          description: Successful request
      summary: Intezer Analyze Download File by SHA256
  tmp5:
    post:
      description: Enables you to generate a vaccine for a specific file. The request
        and response are according to the structure defined in the Request and Response
        Structure section.
      parameters:
      - description: The ID of an analysis
        example: 768a3ba4-d80a-4ca6-b87c-22f071495705
        in: query
        name: Analysis ID
        required: true
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: The ID of a sub-analysis
        example: 568a3ba4-d80a-4ca6-b87c-22f0712345
        in: query
        name: Sub-Analysis ID
        required: true
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: Specifies the format of the vaccine. The default is the yara.
          Other options are - open_ioc, stix, stix2
        example: yara
        in: query
        name: Vaccine Format
        required: false
        schema: {type: string}
      responses:
        '200':
          content:
            application/json:
              schema: {$ref: '#/components/schemas/tmp5'}
          description: Successful request
      summary: Intezer Analyze Generate Vaccine
  tmp6:
    post:
      description: The Get Analysis task will retrieve analysis information.
      parameters:
      - description: The ID of an analysis
        example: 768a3ba4-d80a-4ca6-b87c-22f071495705
        in: query
        name: Analysis ID
        required: true
        schema: {type: string}
      responses:
        '200':
          content:
            application/json:
              schema: {$ref: '#/components/schemas/tmp6'}
          description: Successful request
      summary: Intezer Analyze Get Analysis
  tmp7:
    post:
      description: Get Data by File Hash
      parameters:
      - description: MD5, SHA256 hash for file
        example: ''
        in: query
        name: Hash
        required: true
        schema: {type: string}
      responses:
        '200':
          content:
            application/json:
              schema: {$ref: '#/components/schemas/tmp7'}
          description: Successful request
      summary: Intezer Analyze Get Analysis Data by File Hash
  tmp8:
    post:
      description: Get Sub-Analysis Related Samples
      parameters:
      - description: The ID of an analysis
        example: 768a3ba4-d80a-4ca6-b87c-22f071495705
        in: query
        name: Analysis ID
        required: true
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: The ID of a sub-analysis
        example: 568a3ba4-d80a-4ca6-b87c-22f0712345
        in: query
        name: Sub-Analysis ID
        required: true
        schema: {type: string}
      responses:
        '200':
          content:
            application/json:
              schema: {$ref: '#/components/schemas/tmp8'}
          description: Successful request
      summary: Intezer Analyze Get Sub-Analysis Related Samples
  tmp9:
    post:
      description: The Get Sub-Analysis task will retrieve all sub-analysis IDs from
        an analysis.
      parameters:
      - description: The ID of an analysis
        example: 768a3ba4-d80a-4ca6-b87c-22f071495705
        in: query
        name: Analysis ID
        required: true
        schema: {type: string}
      responses:
        '200':
          content:
            application/json:
              schema: {$ref: '#/components/schemas/tmp9'}
          description: Successful request
      summary: Intezer Analyze Get Sub-Analyses
tags:
- {name: Investigation}
